div><p class="ds-related-work--metadata ds2-5-body-xs">2020</p><p class="ds2-5-body-sm ds-related-work--abstract ">The world is now more connected than ever in the history, almost 56.1% of the world population has access to the internet Global Internet usage (2019), which resulted in a massive amount of data being produced every second. Analyzing the data to understand and solve real-world problems has taken a new leap. Even though machine learning algorithms are there for many decades in literature, it has revived due to many factors like cheaper computation, big data, growing community, etc in recent years The AI Resurgence: Why Now? (2015). The developed countries have been investing more and more every year on research and development projects in a number of domains related to AI. This project tries to explore Artificial Intelligence (AI) as perceived by countries at present from different perspectives like funding, areas of research and academics. The objective is to analyze which countries are ahead in the applied machine learning or AI race. This information can be used by companies, students or researchers to get a good overview of which country to choose from when it comes to delving into the field of AI.</p><div class="ds-related-work--ctas"><a class="ds2-5-text-link ds2-5-text-link--inline js-tc-loswp--wsj-grid-card-download-pdf-modal js-login-button--a6086a6b"><span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size: 18px" translate="no">download</span><span class="ds2-5-text-link__content">Download free PDF</span></a><script>document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
